# Local Leader — Cursor Agent Rules

## Project Overview

This is an **Astro 4.x** site using **Tailwind CSS 3.x** for **Local Leader**, a local SEO service for Australian tradies (tradespeople). The site maintains **multiple independent landing page designs** with a hub page at `/` that links to each version. Currently v1 and v3 are active — new versions can be added following the pattern below.

**Live site:** localleader.au
**Deployed on:** Railway (auto-deploys from `master` branch)
**Dev server:** `npm run dev` (port 4321, host 0.0.0.0)
**Build:** `npm run build`
**Node:** 20.11.0 (Volta pinned)

---

## Version Architecture

Each version is **fully isolated** — own layout, own page, own components. Versions do NOT share styles, navigation, or layout structure. This means you can completely redesign a version without affecting any other version.

### Directory Structure

```
src/
  layouts/
    Layout.astro          → v1 layout (imports shared Navbar + Footer)
    LayoutV3.astro        → v3 layout (self-contained, no shared nav/footer)

  pages/
    index.astro           → Hub/selector page (links to all versions)
    v1/index.astro        → Version 1 landing page
    v3/index.astro        → Version 3 landing page

  components/
    sections/             → v1 components (Hero, Pricing, FAQ, Testimonials, etc.)
    shared/               → Shared utility components (Button, Container, Paragraph, Title)
    cards/                → Card components (used by v1)
    blocks/               → Block components (used by v1)
    v3/                   → v3-specific components (Hero, Header, LogoCloud, HowItWorks)

public/
  images/                 → Static images
    hero.jpg              → v1 hero image
    hero-v3.jpg           → v3 hero image
    logo.jpg              → v1 logo
    logo-v3.jpg           → v3 logo
```

---

## How to Build a New Version Page

When asked to build a new version (e.g., "build v4"), follow these steps:

1. **Layout** — Create `src/layouts/LayoutV{N}.astro`. Copy LayoutV3 as a template (self-contained, minimal). Change Google Fonts as needed.

2. **Page** — Create `src/pages/v{N}/index.astro`. Import the new layout. Build sections inline here first — you can extract components later.

3. **Components** — As the page grows, extract sections into `src/components/v{N}/ComponentName.astro`. Import them in the page file.

4. **Images** — Add version-specific images to `public/images/` using the naming convention: `hero-v{N}.jpg`, `logo-v{N}.jpg`, etc.

5. **Hub** — After building, add a card linking to `/v{N}` in `src/pages/index.astro`.

6. **VERSIONS.md** — **IMPORTANT:** After building or significantly updating a version, update `VERSIONS.md` in the project root with:
   - Build date
   - Style description
   - Design inspiration
   - Which LLM/model you are (e.g., "Cursor Agent + Claude Sonnet 4.6")
   - Status change (Scaffold → In Progress → Complete)
   - Any notes

---

## Layout Conventions

- Every layout accepts a `title` prop via the Astro `Props` interface
- Layouts provide the HTML shell (`<html>`, `<head>`, `<body>`) with a `<slot />`
- Always include: `lang="en-AU"`, viewport meta, favicon, generator meta, description meta
- Newer versions (v3+) are **self-contained** — navigation and footer are built inline in the page, not imported from shared components
- Google Fonts are loaded in the layout's `<head>` via `<link>` tags

---

## Component Conventions

- Components are `.astro` files in `src/components/v{N}/`
- Components are purely presentational — no data fetching
- Use **Tailwind utility classes exclusively** for styling
- Each component is a self-contained section (Hero, Features, Pricing, FAQ, etc.)
- Keep frontmatter minimal; accept props only when needed

---

## Styling

- **Tailwind CSS 3.x** — primary styling method
- `darkMode: "class"` is configured but all versions are **light mode**
- Custom Tailwind colors: `primary: "#1A73E8"` (Google blue)
- Custom breakpoint: `midmd: 880px`

### Current Font Pairings

| Version | Primary Font | Accent Font | Visual Feel |
|---------|-------------|-------------|-------------|
| v1 | Raleway | — | Classic SaaS |
| v3 | Inter | Playfair Display | Premium minimal |

New versions should use a **distinct font pairing** not already in use. Good options include: DM Sans, Space Grotesk, Plus Jakarta Sans, Outfit, Satoshi, General Sans paired with serif accents like Lora, Crimson Pro, DM Serif Display, Source Serif Pro.

---

## Business Context

Use this information when writing copy for any version:

- **Company:** Local Leader
- **Service:** Local SEO for Australian tradies (tradespeople)
- **Target audience:** Plumbers, electricians, builders, roofers, landscapers — trade professionals in Australia
- **Three pillars:**
  1. **Top of Google Maps** — Rank in the top 3 for local searches
  2. **First Page of Google Search** — Organic traffic, no ad spend
  3. **5-Star Review Engine** — Automated review collection from happy clients
- **Pricing:** $999/month, no lock-in contracts
- **CTA:** "Book Your Free Strategy Call"
- **Headline pattern:** "Become the #1 tradie in your area"
- **Pain point:** Tradies are chasing work instead of choosing it
- **Tone:** Professional, confident, results-focused. Speak directly to the tradie. Avoid marketing jargon. Be Australian.

---

## Design Guidelines

When building a version, aim for a **distinctive, high-quality design** that could be a real production landing page. Each version should feel different from the others. Consider varying:

- Layout direction (centered hero vs. split hero vs. asymmetric)
- Color palette (light vs. dark vs. bold accent colors)
- Typography scale and weight
- Section ordering and content density
- Visual elements (cards, stats, charts, testimonials, logos, images)
- Animation and interaction patterns

Reference high-quality landing pages from companies like Linear, Vercel, Stripe, Notion, or Framer for inspiration. Avoid generic "template" aesthetics.

---

## Technical Notes

- Astro 4.x with **file-based routing** — each `index.astro` in a directory becomes a route
- TypeScript available but not required for page/component files
- Prettier configured with Astro plugin for formatting
- Images in `public/` are served as-is; images in `src/assets/` go through Astro's image optimization
